### üöÄ START FILES - CRITICAL RULES
**MANDATORY RULE - STRICTLY ENFORCED**:
- **System MUST NOT have several start files**
- **Exactly TWO start files allowed**:
  1. **`start.bat`** / **`start.sh`** (Root) - Simple start (basic development server, no Docker)
  2. **`dev_server/start_dev_server.bat`** / **`dev_server/start_dev_server.sh`** - Full development server (starts EVERYTHING with Docker Compose)
- **NO other start files allowed** - This is CRITICAL

**Start File Rules**:
- ‚úÖ **`start.bat`** (Windows) / **`start.sh`** (Mac/Linux) - Simple start, detects best server (Node.js ‚Üí Python ‚Üí PHP), no Docker
- ‚úÖ **`stop.bat`** (Windows) / **`stop.sh`** (Mac/Linux) - Stop simple server (stops processes on port 8000)
- ‚úÖ **`dev_server/start_dev_server.bat`** (Windows) / **`dev_server/start_dev_server.sh`** (Mac/Linux) - Full start, Docker Compose, starts ALL services
- ‚úÖ **`dev_server/stop_dev_server.bat`** (Windows) / **`dev_server/stop_dev_server.sh`** (Mac/Linux) - Stop full dev server (stops all Docker containers)
- ‚ùå **NO additional start files** (e.g., `start_frontend.bat`, `start_backend.bat`, `run.bat`, `launch.bat`)
- ‚ùå **NO start files in other locations** (frontend/, backend/, service folders)
- ‚ùå **NO service-specific start files** (use Docker Compose commands instead)
- ‚ùå **NO platform-specific start files** (must support Windows, Mac, and Linux)
- ‚ùå **NO start files without corresponding stop files** (every start file must have a stop file)

**Cross-Platform Requirements**:
- ‚úÖ **Windows**: `.bat` files for batch scripts
- ‚úÖ **Mac/Linux**: `.sh` files for shell scripts
- ‚úÖ **Both platforms must have identical functionality**
- ‚úÖ **Start scripts must detect platform and use appropriate commands**

**See `docs/Setup & Configuration/START_FILES_RULES.md` for complete start files rules.**

