## Development Server

### Running the Project Locally
- **Windows**: Use `start.bat` - automatically detects and uses best available server
- **Mac/Linux**: Use `start.sh` - automatically detects and uses best available server
- **Node.js**: `node server.js` - transpiles TypeScript on the fly using esbuild
- **Python**: `python -m http.server 8000` - static file server (TypeScript won't work)
- **Fallback**: `npx http-server -p 8000` - if Node.js server fails
- **Full Environment**: Use `dev_server/start_dev_server.bat` (Windows) or `dev_server/start_dev_server.sh` (Mac/Linux) for Docker Compose

### TypeScript Transpilation
- **Development**: `server.js` uses esbuild to transpile `.ts` and `.tsx` files on demand
- **Production**: `build.js` pre-builds all TypeScript files to JavaScript in `dist/` folder
- Files are bundled with dependencies but CDN packages (React, ReactDOM, Recharts) are marked external
- Transpiled files are cached for performance
- Errors are logged with detailed messages for debugging

### Production Build
- Run `npm run build` to build for production
- Outputs to `dist/` directory
- TypeScript files are transpiled to JavaScript
- Static files are copied to dist folder
- Ready for deployment to Netlify or other static hosts

